body:
```
$ verilator --version
Verilator 5.028 2024-08-21 rev UNKNOWN.REV
```

[I have a simple 80-line UART Transmitter](https://gist.github.com/nickelpro/ce7677305dd57c2ba71eca46a062471a)

The final `always_comb` block, lines 69-79, are of concern:

```verilog
always_comb begin
  case (curState)
    IDLE: nextState = enterStart ? START : curState;

    START: nextState = DATA;

    DATA: nextState = |writeCount ? curState : STOP;

    STOP: nextState = enterStart ? START : IDLE;
  endcase
end
```

When verilating with `verilator --coverage --cc UartTx.sv`, we can see the coverage is correctly inserted for this block:
```cpp
vlSelf->__vlCoverInsert(&(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[45]), first, "UartTx.sv", 71, 11, ".UartTx", "v_line/UartTx", "case", "71");
vlSelf->__vlCoverInsert(&(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[46]), first, "UartTx.sv", 73, 12, ".UartTx", "v_line/UartTx", "case", "73");
vlSelf->__vlCoverInsert(&(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[47]), first, "UartTx.sv", 75, 11, ".UartTx", "v_line/UartTx", "case", "75");
vlSelf->__vlCoverInsert(&(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[48]), first, "UartTx.sv", 77, 11, ".UartTx", "v_line/UartTx", "case", "77");
vlSelf->__vlCoverInsert(&(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[49]), first, "UartTx.sv", 69, 3, ".UartTx", "v_line/UartTx", "block", "69-70");
```

The logic for the block itself is generated as a ConstPool lookup, and the counts for these coverage points are not updated when evaluating that lookup:
```cpp
__Vtableidx1 = (((IData)(vlSelfRef.UartTx__DOT__writeCount) 
                    << 3U) | (((IData)(vlSelfRef.UartTx__DOT__enterStart) 
                            << 2U) | (IData)(vlSelfRef.UartTx__DOT__curState)));
vlSelfRef.UartTx__DOT__nextState = VUartTx__ConstPool__TABLE_h5f91972e_0
    [__Vtableidx1];
```
I would expect to see:
```cpp
++(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[45]);
++(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[46]);
// ...
++(vlSymsp->__Vcoverage[49]);
```

Nowehere in the generated code is an increment for these coverage points inserted, making it impossible to write tests to satisfy a coverage report.
